Honored to be named the 2025 Outstanding Congressional Champion by the United Spinal Association, alongside my friend and fellow Disabilities Caucus Co-Chair, @RepDebDingell.

@UnitedSpinal traces it roots back to our hero WWII veterans who returned home to an inaccessible nation and turned that struggle into a mission to build a more inclusive society. That mission continues today—empowering the 5.5 million wheelchair users across the country through advocacy, resources, and support.

I’ve been proud to work alongside United Spinal to expand access to assistive technology, invest in home and community-based care, and deliver the resources the disability community needs to thrive. We’ve fought side by side to advance inclusion, independence, and dignity—and that fight continues. Thank you for this honor, my friends.

@BAPSCharities continues to raise the bar—turning compassion into impact and bringing people together to make a real difference. 

Yesterday, our community once again came together for the BAPS Charities Annual Spirit of Service: Walk-Run, this time in Warrington. Over $11,000 was raised to support Warrington Township Emergency Services and the Warrington Community Ambulance Corps—an incredible non-profit made that has been providing lifesaving care to families across Bucks and Montgomery Counties since 1971.

My sincere thanks to the entire BAPS team for your continued dedication and partnership, and to everyone who showed up to support this powerful cause.

