Service has the power to unite us, and this morning in Lansdale, that spirit was on full display at the BAPS Charities Annual Spirit of Service: Walk-Run. With over 300 neighbors walking and running to support the Autism Cares Foundation and Liz's Birthday Closet, this event was a reminder of what’s possible when a community comes together to uplift others.

@BAPSCharities doesn’t just speak the language of service—they lead by example. From food drives and health initiatives to global relief efforts, they’ve been a vital partner in our shared mission and efforts to make a difference in our community and build a more compassionate, connected world.

Thank you to the entire BAPS team for all your efforts, and to all who showed up to support—especially my buddy Evan Rothholz!

Set to open in 2025, the Bright Path Center will revolutionize access to mental health care in our community, offering a welcoming, supportive environment designed to de-escalate and stabilize. I’m proud to have secured $1M for this first-of-its-kind facility, which unites multiple essential crisis services under one roof. Together, withLenape Valley Foundation,
@DoylestownHlth, the Bucks County Department of Behavioral Health/Developmental Programs, & other community partners, we’re bringing life-changing support to our community—ensuring a brighter, healthier future for children, adults, & families in crisis.

